  "parity_obstruction": {
    "direct_<2s_2p_0|g|2p_-1_2p_+1>": 0.0,
    "exchange_<2s_2p_0|g|2p_+1_2p_-1>": 0.0,
    "sum (matrix element)": 0.0,
    "parity_obstruction": "The 2s2p -> 2p^2 transition requires changing (0,1) -> (1,1) on electron 1 and (1,1) -> (1,-1)... wait, let me redo.  For direct: e1 goes 2s(l=0,m=0) -> 2p(l=1,m=-1), so l1+l3 = 0+1 = 1 (odd).  e2 goes 2p(l=1,m=0) -> 2p(l=1,m=+1), so l2+l4 = 1+1 = 2 (even).  For any single k, both l1+l3+k and l2+l4+k must be even -- impossible if (l1+l3) and (l2+l4) have different parity."
  },
